stylometry: @RISK shows the risks involved with the different inputs in the simulation model. It does this by running as many iterations of the model per each input (usually about 1000 iterations), so if you are analyzing 5 inputs, it will run 1,000 iterations for each. After the 5,000 iterations are run, @RISK shows the results in the bell curve, with different variables (like standard deviation) being analyzed. By running thousands of possible answers quickly through this program, managers are better able to analyze the risks associated with their model and management strategies.
